I am a busy person with a lot of things to do and I hardly have the time to go down into the field to verify the work of CILSS (Inter-State Committee for Drought Control in the Sahel). The second problem I face is of wilful procrastination. A project I recommend is approved and we do not hurry to execute it. For instance, about 17 years now we have had heliotropism in the country and we still continue to wait for that project.
Saving farming jobs The growing scarcity of agricultural jobs is one of our major problems. Farmers I have interviewed recently do not leave their farms, but lack hoes and knowledge of farming. In fact, farmers now depend more on immediate sales and so they cannot even bother with stocks or storing of surplus farming produce. The major marketing problems are transportation and storage. Finally, transport, storage, marketing, CILSS and irrigation system in the areas are underdeveloped.
Patching up the cracks The major reforms to engage youth in farming should focus on providing support and tractors to farmers. The community authority should be involved. Also, gendered agricultural support is a major concern because while women provide the labour for farming, they hardly own the land. This reduces their work and increases their income, but at the disadvantage of the
